public class OAViewDefImpl
extends oracle.jbo.server.ViewDefImpl

A common implementation of the view object definition class. This class encapsulates the additional processing of the persisted definition. The processed information may be cached in an object of this class to improve performance. This class can also be used as a template for creating persistable view definitions at runtime.

See Also:
OAViewObjectImpl, OAViewRowImpl

setTransientProperty

public static void setTransientProperty(oracle.jbo.server.ViewDefImpl viewDef,
                                        java.lang.String key,
                                        java.lang.Object value)
Sets a transient property. If this view definition is to be persisted, removeAllTransientProperties must be called to remove all transient properties; otherwise an exception may be thrown for the property values that are not String objects.

Parameters:
viewDef - the view definition
key - the property key
value - the property value. The value should not be null.
Throws:
java.lang.NullPointerException - if the given view definition or key is null
